Sixth Avenue, east side, north from W. 25th St., as photographed before and after the removal of the old "El" line. The Empire State Building towers over the district in the later view. At the left appears the Hotel McAlpin at Greeley Square.

Sixth Avenue, west side, north from West 25th Street, showing same subsequent to the "El" removal. Note the bus replacing the former surface cars. The tracks for the latter have not been removed.
View 2 is limited to the 25th -26th Street block.
